# Raia Abu Ahmad | Semantic Scholar

[

## Toward FAIR Semantic Publishing of Research Dataset Metadata in the Open Research Knowledge Graph

](/paper/Toward-FAIR-Semantic-Publishing-of-Research-Dataset-Ahmad-D'Souza/d102624b80f03555a95c202ff85dc3aad87f4c29)

[Raia Abu Ahmad](/author/Raia-Abu-Ahmad/2238986612)[Jennifer D'Souza](/author/Jennifer-D'Souza/2269984130) [Sören Auer](/author/S%C3%B6ren-Auer/2268415251)

Computer Science, Environmental Science

-   12 April 2024

This work aims to establish a standardized framework for recording and reporting research datasets within the ORKG-Dataset content type, a specialized branch of the Open Research Knowledge Graoh (ORKG) platform, which provides descriptive information and a semantic model for research datasets, integrating them with their accompanying scholarly publications.

[

## FoRC4CL: A Fine-grained Field of Research Classification and Annotated Dataset of NLP Articles

](/paper/FoRC4CL%3A-A-Fine-grained-Field-of-Research-and-of-Ahmad-Borisova/6740ac2b307eacd4023cd517bc8a7c5e8190c15c)

[Raia Abu Ahmad](/author/Raia-Abu-Ahmad/2238986612)[Ekaterina Borisova](/author/Ekaterina-Borisova/2238686258)[Georg Rehm](/author/Georg-Rehm/2238737344)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   2024

A corpus of 1,500 ACL Anthology publications annotated with their main contributions is constructed using a novel hierarchical taxonomy of core CL/NLP topics and sub-topics to classify papers into their respective sub-topics.

[

## Joint Proceedings of the Onto4FAIR 2023 Workshops

](/paper/Joint-Proceedings-of-the-Onto4FAIR-2023-Workshops-Trojahn-Bonino/d4861f92167bb59004c9525ffb5610a96e295018)

[C. Trojahn](/author/C.-Trojahn/3469495)[Luiz Bonino](/author/Luiz-Bonino/2269978759) [Sören Auer](/author/S%C3%B6ren-Auer/2268415251)

Computer Science

This paper presents an extension of the Metadata for Ontology Description and Publication Ontology incorporating this profile as well as its implementation and its use to build FAIRcat, a prototype of a FAIR Data Point harvesting the content of multiple semantic artefact catalogues.

[

## Open Science Best Practices in Data Science and Artificial Intelligence

](/paper/Open-Science-Best-Practices-in-Data-Science-and-Borisova-Ahmad/c51ea3693caba0bf1181580f4a8a9329ec4b6226)

[Ekaterina Borisova](/author/Ekaterina-Borisova/2238686258)[Raia Abu Ahmad](/author/Raia-Abu-Ahmad/2238986612)[Georg Rehm](/author/Georg-Rehm/2238737344)

Computer Science

CoRDI

-   7 September 2023

This paper focuses on Data Science and Artificial Intelligence Open Science best practices, i.e., a set of recommendations that eventually contribute to the management and development of digital artefacts that are as FAIR as possible.

## NFDI4DS Infrastructure and Services

](/paper/NFDI4DS-Infrastructure-and-Services-Schimmler-Wentzel/f1e5236a859658c35e5e6d6679da03da740af39a)

[Sonja Schimmler](/author/Sonja-Schimmler/2290288949)[Bianca Wentzel](/author/Bianca-Wentzel/2238644392) [Matthias Lieber](/author/Matthias-Lieber/2290288841)

Computer Science, Law

GI-Jahrestagung

-   2023

The goals of NFDI4DS are presented, and an overview on what the consortium is going to contribute to the data science and artificial intelligence communities are given, which focuses on existing and newly developed services and their integration.

[

## NFDI4DS Transfer and Application

](/paper/NFDI4DS-Transfer-and-Application-Borisova-Ahmad/7ffc54342c83246a3802aa8ce835adb4e14157c8)

[Ekaterina Borisova](/author/Ekaterina-Borisova/2238686258)[Raia Abu Ahmad](/author/Raia-Abu-Ahmad/2238986612) [Sonja Schimmler](/author/Sonja-Schimmler/2290288949)

Computer Science, Engineering

GI-Jahrestagung

-   2023

This paper describes the main actions taken to engage with the relevant (sub)communities of the NFDI4DS project to build a bridge between NFDI4DS and other research communities which actively apply DS and AI methods.
